{"article_id":"KuVtvB91S4NJyl5r","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In refusing to overturn the temporary restraining order against President Trump 's travel ban ,","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 9th Circuit emphasized an argument","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"that has received relatively little attention in coverage of the case .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"Washington and Minnesota ,","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"which brought the lawsuit","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"that resulted in the TRO ,","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"say","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"many of the people","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"covered by the ban","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"have a right to due process","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"that the government has not even pretended to respect .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"The 9th Circuit thinks","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"the states have a good shot","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"at proving that claim .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"It concludes","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"that `` the Government has not demonstrated","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that the States lack viable claims","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"based on the due process rights of persons","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"who will suffer injuries to protected interests due to the Executive Order . ''","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"In addition to suspending the admission of refugees for 120 days ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Trump 's order imposes a 90-day ban on travelers from seven overwhelmingly Muslim countries :","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Iran , Iraq , Libya , Somalia , Sudan , Syria , and Yemen .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Washington and Minnesota argue","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that the order impermissibly discriminates against Muslims , a claim","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that has generated much public debate .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"The 9th Circuit thinks","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"`` the States ' claims raise serious allegations","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"and present significant constitutional questions , ''","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"and it rejects the government 's position","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"that judges","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"weighing those questions","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"should pay no attention to public statements","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"made by Trump and his advisers .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"But the appeals court devotes nearly three times as much space to the due process argument .","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"The 9th Circuit notes","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"that the ability","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"to re-enter the country","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"after going abroad ,","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"or to travel in anticipation of that ability ,","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"is a `` liberty interest ''","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"protected by the Fifth Amendment .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Yet `` the Government has not shown","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"that the Executive Order provides what due process requires , such as notice and a hearing prior to restricting an individual 's ability","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"to travel . ''","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"In fact , `` the Government does not contend","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"that the Executive Order provides for such process , ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"since `` the Government argues","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"that most or all of the individuals","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"affected by the Executive Order","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"have no rights under the Due Process Clause . ''","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"The appeals court was not persuaded by that argument .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"Foreign nationals","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"who are outside the United States","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"and have never lived there ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"such as would-be visitors","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"applying for visas","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"or refugees","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"seeking permission","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"to resettle in the U.S. ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"can not assert due process rights .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"according to the Supreme Court ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"the 9th Circuit notes ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"`` The procedural protections","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"provided by the Fifth Amendment 's Due Process Clause","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"are not limited to citizens .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"Rather , they 'appl [ y ] to all 'persons ' within the United States , including aliens , '","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"regardless of 'whether their presence here is lawful , unlawful , temporary , or permanent . '","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"These rights also apply to certain aliens","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"attempting to reenter the United States","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"after travelling abroad . ''","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"In the 1982 case Landon v. Placencia , for example , the Supreme Court held","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"that a lawful permanent resident had a right to due process","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"when the Immigration and Naturalization Service tried to stop her from returning to the United States after `` a brief visit to Mexico","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"that involved an attempt","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"to smuggle aliens across the border . ''","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"The Trump administration initially said","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"the travel ban applied to lawful permanent residents .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Then it issued a blanket waiver","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"their entry is `` in the national interest . ''","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"The administration 's latest position ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"laid out in a February 1 memo from White House Counsel Donald F. McGahn II ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"is that the order never applied to lawful permanent residents .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"The 9th Circuit rejected that assurance ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"questioning McGahn 's authority","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"to revise Trump 's order","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"or to require","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"that other government officials adhere to his interpretation .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"`` Moreover , ''","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"it says ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"`` in light of the Government 's shifting interpretations of the Executive Order , we can not say","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"that the current interpretation by White House counsel ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"even if authoritative and binding ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"will persist past the immediate stage of these proceedings . ''","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"In any case ,","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"the appeals court says ,","depth":5},{"id":97,"text":"green-card holders are not the only people","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"affected by the order with potential due process claims .","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"They also include `` non-immigrant visaholders","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"who have been in the United States","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"but temporarily departed","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"or wish to temporarily depart ''","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"( such as foreign nationals","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"working in the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"or attending American universities )","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"and `` applicants","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"who have a relationship with a U.S. resident or an institution","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that might have rights of its own","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"to assert ''","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"( such as relatives of citizens or scholars","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"hired by American universities ) .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"Even refugees could make due process claims under 18 USC 1231","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"if they seek asylum","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"after arriving in the United States .","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"`` The Government has provided no affirmative argument","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"showing","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"that the States ' procedural due process claims fail as to these categories of aliens , ''","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"the 9th Circuit says .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"`` For example , the Government has failed to establish","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"that lawful permanent residents have no due process rights","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"when seeking to re-enter the United States .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"Nor has the Government established","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"that the Executive Order provides lawful permanent residents with constitutionally sufficient process","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"to challenge their denial of re-entry . ''","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"Assuming that some people affected by the order","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"have a right to due process ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"it is not clear what it would entail .","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"The only potential relief","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"provided by the order","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"comes from discretionary , case-by-case waivers `` in the national interest . ''","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"The 9th Circuit suggests","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"that due process would at least require `` notice and a hearing prior","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"to restricting an individual 's ability","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"to travel , ''","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"and presumably the hearing would do more","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"than verify","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"that the individual comes from one of the banned countries .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"The Trump administration asked the appeals court ,","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"if it was not prepared to block the TRO entirely ,","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"to narrow its scope","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"so that it covers only `` previously admitted aliens","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"who are temporarily abroad now","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"or who wish to travel and return to the United States in the future . ''","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"That category would include many of the people with potential due process claims ,","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"the 9th Circuit notes ,","depth":6},{"id":146,"text":"but not all of them ,","depth":5},{"id":147,"text":"since it omits `` aliens","depth":7},{"id":148,"text":"who are in the United States unlawfully , ''","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"who `` have due process rights as well , ''","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"and `` citizens","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"who have an interest in specific non-citizens ' ability","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"to travel to the United States . ''","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"Rather than seek a narrower TRO ,","depth":4},{"id":154,"text":"Trump could rewrite his order","depth":6},{"id":155,"text":"to focus on unvetted foreign nationals","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"who have never visited the U.S. ,","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"which would address most of the due process concerns","depth":6},{"id":158,"text":"while bolstering the credibility of his claim","depth":7},{"id":159,"text":"that he is trying to protect Americans from terrorists .","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"`` Even if the TRO might be overbroad in some respects , ''","depth":6},{"id":161,"text":"the 9th Circuit says ,","depth":6},{"id":162,"text":"`` it is not our role to try , in effect , to rewrite the Executive Order .","depth":5},{"id":163,"text":"The political branches are far better equipped","depth":5},{"id":164,"text":"to make appropriate distinctions . ''","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":329,"left":302,"right":328,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":259,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuc